29/01/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- Chief of General Staff General Hilmi Ozkok met with his visiting Bulgarian counterpart Nikola Kolev on Wednesday (28 January) to discuss the idea of Turkish anti-terrorist instructors training Bulgarian contingents headed to Iraq. They also discussed bilateral military and technical co-operation, including joint training and personnel exchanges.
Also Wednesday, the energy ministers of Bulgaria and Turkey met in Istanbul to discuss the resumption of electricity supplies, suspended last spring. (Anadolu Agency, BTA, BNR - 28/01/04)
